  "smoking_guns": [
    {
      "id": "SG-001",
      "severity": "critical",
      "title": "Dual predicate evaluation systems — old inline vs new typed resolvers",
      "description": "state-machine.ts contains evaluatePredicate() (lines 308-409) with inline boolean logic for each predicate kind. But the file also imports checkPredicate from './predicates' (line 11). The LANE_STATE_MACHINE spec uses string predicate names (e.g., 'plan_produced') that are evaluated by the OLD evaluatePredicate. Meanwhile, predicates.ts defines a complete typed predicate resolver map (lines 651-668) with evidence tracking that is NOT wired into the state machine reducer (reduceCampaignState). These are two parallel, incompatible predicate engines.",
      "files": ["packages/opencode/src/campaign/state-machine.ts:11,308", "packages/opencode/src/campaign/predicates.ts:651"]
    },
    {
      "id": "SG-002",
      "severity": "high",
      "title": "plan.produced predicate is ambiguous across 3 transitions",
      "description": "The 'plan_produced' predicate fires from both ScoutComplete (toSMEvent line 156) and ArchitectComplete (toSMEvent line 158). The LANE_STATE_MACHINE uses it for 3 different transitions: scouting→scoped (line 132), scoped→planning (line 138), planning→critic (line 144). There is no role-based disambiguation — the SM relies solely on current state context to differentiate. If a cartographer emits plan.produced while the SM is in 'planning', it would incorrectly trigger planning→critic.",
      "files": ["packages/opencode/src/campaign/state-machine.ts:132,138,144", "packages/opencode/src/campaign/secretary.ts:156,158"]
    },
    {
      "id": "SG-003",
      "severity": "high",
      "title": "addEvidence 'executionEvents' and 'transitionEvents' only populated at terminal state",
      "description": "In secretary.ts, processEvent only calls binderService.addEvidence for 'transitionEvents' (line 492) and 'executionEvents' (line 503) when isTerminal(newState) is true (line 489). This means intermediate transitions accumulate NO evidence in the binder — the binder is only populated as a post-hoc summary. If a lane crashes before reaching terminal state, all evidence is lost.",
      "files": ["packages/opencode/src/campaign/secretary.ts:489,492,503"]
    },
    {
      "id": "SG-004",
      "severity": "medium",
      "title": "Event name inconsistency: CampaignLaneCreated = 'lane.created'",
      "description": "In event-names.ts line 98, CampaignLaneCreated has value 'lane.created' (not 'campaign.lane.created'). This breaks the campaign.* namespace convention where all other campaign events use the 'campaign.' prefix. The toSMEvent mapping at secretary.ts:130 maps LaneCreated → 'lane.created', matching the (inconsistent) event name.",
      "files": ["packages/opencode/src/event/event-names.ts:98", "packages/opencode/src/campaign/secretary.ts:130"]
    },
    {
      "id": "SG-005",
      "severity": "medium",
      "title": "addEvidence section parameter is untyped string — no compile-time safety",
      "description": "The Interface.addEvidence signature (binder.ts line 149-152) accepts `section: string`. The actual allowed sections are enforced only at runtime via switch/case (lines 322-366). An invalid section name will only fail at runtime with a BinderError. The typed predicate system in predicates.ts could validate this at compile time but isn't integrated.",
      "files": ["packages/opencode/src/campaign/binder.ts:149,321-366"]
    },
    {
      "id": "SG-006",
      "severity": "low",
      "title": "evaluatePredicate references event types not in EventName registry",
      "description": "evaluatePredicate (state-machine.ts:308-409) matches on string literals like 'session.checkpoint' (line 199), 'claims.acquired' (line 337), 'scope.unsafe' (line 370). These strings are NOT in the canonical EventName registry at event-names.ts. They are ad-hoc event types that exist only in the SM's internal event model.",
      "files": ["packages/opencode/src/campaign/state-machine.ts:199,337,370", "packages/opencode/src/event/event-names.ts"]
    }
  ],

